  "wraps": {
    "packages": [
      "guzzlehttp/guzzle ^7.8 (HTTP client for provider dispatch — retry-safe, connection-pooled, request-signable)"
    ],
    "rationale": "Every provider driver dispatches through a shared Guzzle client with per-provider timeout + retry-safe request encoding. The `MonitoringPayloadTransformer` builds the provider-native payload; the driver hands it to Guzzle which handles TLS + connection pooling + timeout. Retry semantics for provider notifications are OWNED BY THIS MODULE (via RetryFailedNotificationsJob + backoff schedule) — Guzzle-level retry is disabled to preserve idempotency + circuit-breaker semantics."
